727425f-a.text:
Metropolitan Avenue, at the N.E. corner of 70th Street, showing Henry Schumacher's Hotel, known as Martins Hotel in 1924, of which Martin Blaum was the proprietor. The building was sold in December 1924 to Dietrich anc Son, nickel platers. This is a set of two views. In view No. 2 is seen the gate to the Old Lutheran Cemetery.
1922
View 21 October 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
(3) Another view, at a later date.
P.L.Sperr  July 2, 1935

727426f-b.text:
Eetropolitan Avenue, north side, west of 70th Street, showing beyond the second stone yard Siebs Hotel, known also as the Central Hotel. C.F. and J.N.F. Siebs owned it respectively in 1873 and 1896-1898. Christian F. Siebs was born in Germany in 1831 and immigrated here in 1855. He began at this corner with 4 rooms which he gradually enlwrged. He died in 1889. Views 3 and 4 look in the
opposite direction from 69th Street.
Feb. 1925.
Views 1,3 and 4
View 21 1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
